    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`vim.pack` currently uses `git clone --filter=blob:none --recurse-submodules --also-filter-submodules` to clone packages. `--also-filter-submodules` was introduced in git 2.36 which was [released in April 2022](https://github.com/git/git/releases/tag/v2.36.0). Thus, `vim.pack` requires git>=2.36. 2022 is not that long ago, and there are likely a lot of environments where just an older version of `git` is available. (I noticed this on a Ubuntu 22.04 machine, where [only git 2.34 can be installed from official sources](https://packages.ubuntu.com/jammy-updates/git).)\n\nFrom [this comment](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/36389#issuecomment-3467184543), it seems that both `--filter` and `--also-filter-submodules` especially are optimizations to speed up the cloning process. (`lazy.nvim` also used to clone with `--also-filter-submodules` but this [was deemed unnecessary and removed](https://github.com/folke/lazy.nvim/issues/83#issuecomment-1362494095).) Perhaps this option can be omitted entirely, or just added when the available git is known to support them?\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe built-in `vim.pack` should be compatible with as many git versions as possible. As a user, I'd like my configuration to work in as many environments as possible.",
