            "body": "I think in this case, the minor performance optimization is not worth the support headache. (I agree that conditional flags are undesirable here.) It's less a case of \"Ubuntu 22.04 must be supported!\" than of avoiding \"I'm on Ubuntu 22.04 why is this marquee feature you hyped up in your release notes not working for me!!eleven!\"\n\nIf even @folke -- who likes to squeeze every ounce of performance out of his plugins ;) -- doesn't deem that flag worth it, I think we can safely ignore it (for now; can always be revisited if the cost-benefit matrix changes for any reason).",
