        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> We can easily check the `git` version with:\n> \n> ```\n> vim.version.parse(vim.fn.system('git --version'))\n> ```\n> \n> so we can have both?\n\nYes, this was addressed in my initial comment:\n\n> Dropping the `--also-filter-submodules` for older Git versions is possible, but requires extra code that can not be (reasonably and reliably) tested and will become only more outdated as the time passes.\n\nIt will require a bit more than `vim.version.parse(vim.fn.system('git --version'))` (and probably not via `vim.fn.system`, but via local `git_cmd`), but doable of course. Is this okay to include in `vim.pack`? This is what [is done in `mini.deps`](https://github.com/nvim-mini/mini.nvim/blob/dce9bc4e19d02d5c37fe71c16f40f8a5536b0386/lua/mini/deps.lua#L906-L909) (and was added when Ubuntu 22.04 was the latest LTS release), but I did not include it in `vim.pack` for the reasons I mentioned above.",
